track_notes: Parking in the layby opposite the track to the radio masts. There are no signs so I would advise to mark the start in the GPS to locate it on the busy A77 road. This was my route down to avoid the worst of the tussocks. About 50min walk.

Parking above Knocklaugh Farm on the grass verge or through gateposts, downhill where there is room ot park on the hairpin bend at the bottom of the hill nearer to the field gate on to the hill. One easy wall to climb on this route. More info about Grey Hill on Catterblog - find using Google Search.
